{{der-top|Compounds}}
* {{ja-r|嘯吹|うそふき}}: the [[clownish]] “[[whistling]]” [[mask]] used in {{m|ja|狂言|tr=kyōgen|lit=crazy talk||a farce performed between [[noh]] plays}}
* {{ja-r|嘯笛|うそぶえ}}: [[whistling]] with one's [[mouth]]
* {{ja-r|息嘯|おきそ}}: a [[sigh]]
* {{ja-r|海嘯|かいしょう}}, {{ja-r|海嘯|つなみ}}: a [[tsunami]], a [[tidal wave]]; a [[tidal bore]]
* {{ja-r|吟嘯|ぎんしょう}}: to [[sing]] or [[chant]] a [[poem]] or [[song]]; to [[wail]] in [[grief]]
* {{ja-r|虎嘯|こしょう}}: a [[tiger]]'s [[roar]]; {{qualifier|metaphor}} a [[hero]]'s [[appearance]]
* {{ja-r|嘯聚|しょうしゅ}}: [[calling]] [[people]] [[together]] {{qualifier|especially by whistling}}
* {{ja-r|嘯集|しょうしゅう}}: [[calling]] [[people]] [[together]] {{qualifier|especially by whistling}}
* {{ja-r|嘯風弄月|しょうふう ろうげつ}}: [[love]] for [[nature]] and [[poetry]] and other [[elegance]]
* {{ja-r|空嘯|そらうそ}}: [[absent-minded]] [[whistling]]
* {{ja-r|長嘯|ちょうしょう}}: [[whistling]] for a long time; [[singing]] or [[chanting]] for a long time
